        %p Start your documentation template by editing one of the starter files. It won't take more than 15 minutes to start. Read the step-by-step guide:
        %br
          %ul.step-text
            %li
              %h5 Prepare your directory
              %p Start your documentation project by makeing a copy of start-kit folder to your desired directory. This folder contains essential files to develop your documentation based on theDocs.
            %li
              %h5 Choose a layout
              %p
                Decide about your documentation layout. Boxed or full-width? Do you need a sidebar on the left of page, on the right of page, or a page without sidebar? Choose your desired layout from one of the starter files and start by editing it. Even it's better to decide about
                %a{:href => "layout_skin.html"} skin
                right now.
            %li
              %h5 Design your header
